olive oil
2 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
2 packet Mild Chorizo
1 Cucumber
2 Radish
1 Lemon
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Place peeled pumpkin wedges on a lined oven tray.
• Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, cut mild chorizo into 1cm chunks.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Add chorizo and cook until browned, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a large bowl.

• When the pumpkin has 5 minutes remaining, slice cucumber into half-moons. Thinly slice radish. Slice lemon into wedges.
• To the bowl with the chorizo, add cucumber, radish, mixed salad leaves, a generous squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of olive oil. Season to taste.

• Divide chorizo salad between bowls. Top with roast pumpkin.
• Drizzle over dill & parsley mayonnaise. Sprinkle over grated parmesan cheese. Enjoy!